Merge work from Ammon Riley
Original rev  : rc@rc0.org.uk--2004-tdl/tdl--devo--1--patch-8

From: Ammon Riley
Subject: tdl patch
Date: Mon, 26 Jul 2004 21:23:10 -0700

[snip]

I've attached a patch that does that, and fixes a few other small
bugs/features:

    - adds a tdls command as a synonym for tdll (tdls just feels more
      natural to me).

    - added a -R flag to run in read-only mode. Commands that have the
      dirty bit turned on in the command struct are disallowed. Special
      code is added for the process_save function, which was the exception
      to the rule for the dirty bit.

    - fixes a bug where unknown commands are printed incorrectly if
      you also used a flag.

        > tdl -q foo
        Unknown command <-q>
        >

      now says

        > tdl -q foo
        Unknown command <foo>
        >

    - fixed bug where unknown commands are being matched to a known
      command, based on the matchlen field in the command struct.

        tdl> about
        Usage: above <index_to_insert_above> <index_to_move> ...
        tdl>

      this now says

        tdl> about
        tdl: Unknown command <about>
        tdl> abo
        Usage: above <index_to_insert_above> <index_to_move> ...
        tdl>

      I modified the command matching code to match the entire length
      of the command, or the cmds[i].matchlen, whichever is greater.

    - modified the flag parsing to (hopefully) make it easier to add
      flags in the future.

What I *didn't* do was modify the documentation.
